  annotation =  "uses pixie to instument executable and get basic block
    (number of times bb executed), procedure (number of times
    proc executed), call (each distinct call site to number of times
    executed) and global variable (maps each var to number of times
    referenced --- useful for register asignment).   discusses
    ways to estimate bb counts, etc without pixie.  hueristics suck
    on which blocks, callsites are called the most --- do pretty well
    on which globals are the most frequently used and do ok on
    which procedure.  real profilers have problem w/ bb freuqncy,
    though they do well for the top 128.  real programs work
