  REMOVE__volume =      "63",
  REMOVE__number =      "9",
  REMOVE__pages =       "1278-1308",
  REMOVE__month =       sep,
  annotation =  "the paper on protection mechanisms.  very thorough, very good.
    eight design principles for protection systems: (a) economy of mechanism
    (simple design = easier to verify), (b) fail-safe defaults - default
    = lack of access (c) complete mediation every access to every object
    must be checked for authority (d) open design -- design should not
    be secret (e) seperation of privilege (2 keys to unlock more
    secure than 1) (f) least privilege -- if read perms work, just give them
    (g) least common mechanism --- minimize the amount of mechanism common to
    more than one user and depended on by all users (h) psychological
    acceptibility --- users don't like it, won't use it, no security.
    protection = impenetrable wall around each object, door with a guard
    ticket or access control list scheme to permit entry.  tickets diffuse
    accountability.  dynamic authorization of sharing requires lampson's
    shout down the hall."
}
