    outside the domain can only be accessed via capabilities in local list.
    domains lead a second-class existence within processes.  capabilites in
    parameters can be fixed (i.e., bound) to seal the capability so
    that it is accessible only to the domain which gets invoked by the
    operation.   a calling domain can request construction of a domain
