    note ="Subject: automatic retarget [sic]",
    comment = "
        Date: Tue, 25 Oct 1994 14:33:56 -0400
        To: maxp@amsterdam.lcs.mit.edu
        Subject: automatic retarget

    Hi Max,

            Most retargets are to machines that already have a compiler;
    it should be possible to use this existing compiler to automatically
    retarget the new one (modulo some specific information about
    which registers can be used when, etc).  It might be possible
    to throw the superoptimizer at this problem as well: both to
    improve the quality of the generated code and to automatically
    retarget it as well.

            THis would be pretty cool, if you could pull it off.

    Dawson"

